<span class="subhead">MORE THAN HALF OF U.S. HOUSEHOLDS OWN A DIGITAL TELEVISION</span><br>
More than 50 

percent of U.S. households now own a digital  television (DTV), according to new research 

released today by the Consumer  Electronics Association (CEA)<sup>&#174</sup>. As the nation 

transitions to digital television, consumers are adding  DTV to their homes at a record pace.<br>
<a href="/press/news/rd_release_detail.asp?id=11425">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<span class="subhead">2008 INTERNATIONAL CES DRAWS TALENT FROM THE BIG SCREEN, TELEVISION  SCREEN, RECORDING STUDIOS AND THE SPORTS FIELDS</span><br>
Award  winning actors, musicians, comedians 

and sports stars all come together at the  2008 International CES<sup>&#174</sup> to experience the hottest products and technologies in  the consumer 

electronics industry.<br>
<a href="/press/news/rd_release_detail.asp?id=11423">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<span class="subhead">WESTERN TECHNOLOGY COMPANIES SHOWCASE THEIR PRODUCTS AT THE 2008 INTERNATIONAL CES</span><br>
Nearly 900 technology companies from the Western region  of the United States  

will showcase their latest consumer electronics products at the 2008  International CES - the world&rsquo;s largest consumer technology tradeshow. Together,  

these exhibitors make the western U.S. the most represented domestic  region at CES and cover more than 30 consumer technology categories, including emerging 

 technologies, gaming hardware and software and digital imaging.<br>
<a href="/press/news/rd_release_detail.asp?id=11421">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<span class="subhead">SOUTHERN TECHNOLOGY COMPANIES SHINE BRIGHTLY AT THE 2008 INTERNATIONAL CES</span><br>
More than 170 technology companies from the Southern region  of the United 

States  will showcase their latest consumer electronics products at the 2008  International CES - the world&rsquo;s largest consumer technology tradeshow. 

Together,  these exhibitors make the Southern U.S. the third  most represented domestic region at CES and cover more than 30 different consumer  technology 

categories, including emerging technologies, gaming hardware and  software and digital imaging.<br>
<a href="/press/news/rd_release_detail.asp?id=11420">Read all about it</a><br><br>

