Association (CEA)<sup>&#174</sup>  today announced that His Excellency Paul Kagame,  President 

of the Republic   of Rwanda, will speak at  the 2008 International CES, as part of the new 

Industry Insider Series program  focused on the role of technology in developing countries.<br>
<a href="/press/news/rd_release_detail.asp?id=11400">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<span class="subhead">CEA ANNOUNCES 2008 INNOVATIONS AWARDS FOR EXCELLENCE IN PRODUCT DESIGN AND ENGINEERING</span><br>
The Consumer Electronics  Association (CEA)<sup>&#174</sup> today announced its 2008 International CES Best  of Innovations Design and Engineering  Award honorees. Sponsored by CEA, producer of the International CES, and  endorsed by the Industrial Designers Society of America (IDSA), the  International CES Innovations awards  honor exceptional product and engineering design in 32 consumer electronics  product categories, including new categories such as eco-design and sustainable  technology and healthcare.<br>
<a href="/press/news/rd_release_detail.asp?id=11396">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<span class="subhead">2008 INTERNATIONAL CES GOES GREEN</span><br>
The Consumer  Electronics Association (CEA)<sup>&#174</sup>  today announced that the 2008  International CES<sup>&#174</sup>  is taking unprecedented steps to &quot;go  green&quot; by reducing its carbon&nbsp;footprint and with the use of sustainable  and energy efficient practices.<br>
<a href="/press/news/rd_release_detail.asp?id=11395">Read all about it</a><br><br>

