<span class="subhead">CEA PROJECTS RECORD $22 BILLION IN CONSUMER ELECTRONICS HOLIDAY SALES</span><br>
Consumer  electronics products dominate the holiday wish lists of adults 

and teens and  will generate $48.1 billion in fourth quarter sales, according to research 

from  the Consumer Electronics  Association (CEA)<sup>&#174</sup>. Results from the <em>14th 

Annual CE Holiday Purchase Patterns </em>study were  presented today at CEA&rsquo;s Industry 

Forum, a four-day conference designed to inform,  connect and educate CE professionals, 

industry analysts and the media on the  latest CE trends and technologies.<br>
<a href="/press/news/rd_release_detail.asp?id=11367">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<span class="subhead">CEA EXECUTIVE HONORED WITH PRESTIGIOUS IAEE AWARD</span><br>
The Consumer Electronics Association (CEA)<sup>&#174</sup> congratulates Karen Chupka, senior  vice president, events and conferences, for being named the winner of the 2007  International Association of Exhibitions and Events&rsquo; (IAEE) Outstanding  Achievement in Industry Leadership award.<br>
<a href="/press/news/rd_release_detail.asp?id=11365">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<span class="subhead">HOTTEST DEVELOPMENTS IN  AUDIO STRIKE A CHORD AT THE 2008 INTERNATIONAL CES</span><br>
The latest  technologies and products in audio will sound off at the 2008 International CES<sup>&#174</sup>,  including home theater audio systems, digital music, satellite radio tuners and  audio networking solutions, and the latest in the high-performance audio  category.<br>
<a href="/press/news/rd_release_detail.asp?id=11364">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<span class="subhead">CONTENT AND THE LATEST TECHNOLOGIES CONNECT AT THE 2008 INTERNATIONAL  CES</span><br>
New content  developments from 

major players in the entertainment industry will connect with  the latest distribution platforms at the 2008 International 

CES<sup>&#174</sup>,  making CES the global hub for all that&rsquo;s new in digital entertainment.
<p>As CES&rsquo; first-ever &ldquo;Official  Broadcast Partner,&rdquo; select NBC Universal broadcast and cable entities will 

be  broadcasting live from the CES exhibition floor, covering the many exciting  product debuts and special events.&nbsp; In 

addition,  NBC Universal, one of the world&rsquo;s leading media and entertainment companies,  will debut an interactive and 

multi-faceted show floor exhibition at CES,  highlighting the wide range of digital programming produced by its television,  

cable and motion picture properties.<br>
<a href="/press/news/rd_release_detail.asp?id=11362">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<span class="subhead">DIGITAL ENTERTAINMENT TAKES CENTER STAGE AT THE 2008 INTERNATIONAL CES</span><br>
The latest developments  in the content and digital entertainment industries will 

take center stage at  the 2008 International CES<sup>&#174</sup>, with the largest 

exhibition of digital  entertainment in show history on display, reinforcing CES as the 

global  intersection for the content and technology markets.<br>
<a href="/press/news/rd_release_detail.asp?id=11361">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<span class="subhead">2008 INTERNATIONAL CES   CONFERENCE PROGRAM   HIGHLIGHTS FULL   RANGE OF CONSUMER TECHNOLOGY</span><br>
The 2008 International CES<sup>&#174</sup> today announced its 

extensive lineup  of more than 175 conference sessions designed to help educate attendees on the  latest consumer electronics 

industry trends.<br>
<a href="/press/news/rd_release_detail.asp?id=11357">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<span class="subhead">CEA AND EH PUBLISHING RENEW PARTNERSHIP THROUGH 2011</span><br>
The Consumer Electronics Association (CEA)<sup>&#174</sup> and EH  Publishing, producers of the Electronic House Expo (EHX), today announced the  renewal of their partnership through 2011. Originated in 2002, the partnership  is designed to help foster further growth and development of the consumer electronics industry, including the residential home systems market that EH Publishing specializes in.<br>
<a href="/press/news/rd_release_detail.asp?id=11352">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<span class="subhead">NEW  CEA GIVING PROGRAM WILL PROVIDE CONSUMER ELECTRONICS PRODUCTS TO PEOPLE AND  COMMUNITIES IN NEED</span><br>
The Consumer Electronics 

Association  (CEA)<sup>&#174</sup> today announced that it will launch a new program to  facilitate the charitable donation 

of products from its member companies. This  charitable giving program will be managed by CEA partner Gifts in Kind  

International, a nonprofit organization that receives product donations from  technology, retail and consumer corporations 

and distributes them to more than  150,000 community charities across the United States and throughout the  world. CEA will 

promote the organization&rsquo;s product donation services to its  2,100 member companies.<br>
<a href="/press/news/rd_release_detail.asp?id=11343">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<span class="subhead">COMCAST CHAIRMAN AND CEO BRIAN ROBERTS COMPLETES DYNAMIC KEYNOTE LINEUP  AT THE 2008 INTERNATIONAL CES</span><br>
The Consumer  Electronics Association (CEA)<sup>&#174</sup> announced today that Brian L. Roberts,  chairman and CEO of Comcast Corp., will join the explosive lineup of keynote  speakers at the 2008 International CES. Roberts rounds out the impressive 2008  CES keynote program, which also includes the top executives from Microsoft,  Panasonic, Intel and GM. Owned and produced by CEA, the 2008 International CES,  the world&rsquo;s largest tradeshow for consumer technology, will return to Las Vegas, Nevada,  January 7-10, 2008.<br>
<a href="/press/news/rd_release_detail.asp?id=11338">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<span class="subhead">INNOVATIONS 2008 AWARDS HONOR THE  BEST IN CONSUMER ELECTRONICS </span><br>
Entries for the International 

CES Innovations  2008 Design and Engineering Awards will be accepted today through September 

28,  2007, the Consumer Electronics Association (CEA)<sup>&#174</sup> announced today.  This 

annual competition honors outstanding design and engineering in 32  consumer electronics 

product categories. Healthcare and Eco-Design and Sustainable  Technology are the most 

recent additions to the Innovations awards program.<br>
<a href="/press/news/rd_release_detail.asp?id=11337">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<span class="subhead">GENERAL MOTORS CHAIRMAN AND CEO TO DELIVER KEYNOTE ADDRESS AT THE 2008  INTERNATIONAL CES </span><br>
The Consumer  Electronics 

Association (CEA)<sup>&#174</sup>  announced today that Rick Wagoner,  chairman and CEO of General Motors Corp., will deliver 

a keynote address at the  2008 International CES. Wagoner joins an outstanding lineup of CES keynote  speakers, including 

executives from Microsoft, Panasonic and Intel, slated to make  major presentations at CES.<br>
<a href="/press/news/rd_release_detail.asp?id=11333">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<span class="subhead">TECH GIANTS TOP 2008 INTERNATIONAL CES KEYNOTE SCHEDULE</span><br>
The Consumer  Electronics 

Association (CEA)<sup>&#174</sup> announced today that top executives  from Microsoft, Panasonic and Intel will deliver 

keynote addresses at the 2008  International CES&reg;.<br>
<a href="/press/news/rd_release_detail.asp?id=11315">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<span class="subhead">2008 INTERNATIONAL CES LAUNCHES &ldquo;ART OF  TECHNOLOGY&rdquo; SHOW CAMPAIGN</span><br>
The Consumer Electronics Association (CEA)<sup>&#174</sup> today announced the launch of an innovative new advertising  campaign designed to position the 2008 International CES<sup>&#174</sup> as the largest consumer technology event in the world. Produced by CEA, the International CES is scheduled for January 7-10, 2008, in Las Vegas, Nevada.<br>
<a href="/press/news/rd_release_detail.asp?id=11298">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<span class="subhead">CES AUDIT CONFIRMS LARGEST SHOW FLOOR AND INTERNATIONAL  ATTENDANCE IN CES HISTORY </span><br>
The International CES<sup>&#174</sup> announced 

today the results of an independent audit that confirms CES&rsquo; stature  as the world&rsquo;s largest consumer technology 

tradeshow and North   America&rsquo;s largest annual tradeshow of any kind.&nbsp; The 2007 International CES audit, conducted 

 by VERIS Consulting LLC, revealed that the industry tradeshow drew a record  27,020 international attendees, with overall 

attendance totaling 143,695  industry professionals during CES&rsquo; four-day run in Las Vegas, NV, January 8-11,  

2007.<br>
